organizations.mission:
To promote education, social services, health, and the welfare of communities;
To encourage and advocate for human rights and social change in civil society as a non-governmental organization;
To promote the education and perpetuation of Armenian culture to children, youth, and members;
To enhance the education of the Society’s members and encourage their involvement in public service;
To made special appropriations for food, medicine, and clothing in the event of natural disasters, wars, or epidemics, and to aid the disabled and the ill.
